The paper deals with the use of social media data for disaster management, which falls under the category of social media analytics (cs.SI). The paper also involves the analysis of temporal and spatial correlations between datasets, which could fall under the categories of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses changes in user behavior during severe haze events, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
